    <subfield code="a">Using results in our previous paper “Non-semistable exceptional objects in hereditary categories”, we focus here on studying the topology of the space of Bridgeland stability conditions on <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="italic">Rep</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> , where <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mtext></mtext></math> and k is an algebraically closed field. In particular, we prove that this space is contractible (in the previous paper it was shown that it is connected).</subfield>
